Package org.springframework.social.bitbucket.api

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BitBucket
    Main interface for interacting with BitBucket.
    PrivilegeOperations  
    RepoOperations
    BitBucket sub-API that allows interaction with code repositories.
    UserOperations
    BitBucket sub-API that allows interaction with user accounts.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BitBucketChangeset
    A changeset, aka commit.
    BitBucketChangeset.FileModification
    A modification on a single file.
    BitBucketChangesets
    A container class that holds many changesets as well as information about total number of changesets available.
    BitBucketDirectory
    Metadata about the contents of a repository directory.
    BitBucketFile
    Content as well as metadata about a repository file.
    BitBucketFileMetadata
    Metadata about a file in a repository.
    BitBucketRepository
    A BitBucket repository, possibly with additional metadata.
    BitBucketUser
    A BitBucket user account.
    RepoCreation
    Data object with information needed for repository creation.
    RepoPrivilege  
    UserWithRepositories
    Container class that holds basic information about an account as well as a list of repositories.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    BitBucketChangeset.FileModificationType
    The kind of modification on a file path.
    BitBucketPrivilege
    The type of action that can be taken on a repository.
    BitBucketSCM
    A source control management supported by BitBucket.
